{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a9946d2a-d4fd-4ec3-821f-2533f029610f","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's a general guide for the switch:\n\n### Changes needed for NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. Configure NuGet.org** — Register your GitHub repo as a trusted publisher at:\n`nuget.org → Manage Packages → <package> → Trusted Publishers → Add GitHub repository`\n\nSet the repository owner, name, workflow file path, and optionally the environment.\n\n**2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    # Required for OIDC token\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n    # Optional: lock to a GitHub Environment matching your NuGet config\n    environment: nuget-publish\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # ... build & pack steps ...\n\n      - name: Install .NET\n        uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n\n      - name: Publish to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences from your current setup:**\n\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` used in `--api-key` | No API key needed — remove it |\n| No `permissions` block needed | Add `permissions: id-token: write` |\n| No trusted publisher config on nuget.org | Must register repo on nuget.org |\n\n**3. Remove** the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once everything works.\n\nThe `dotnet nuget push` command in .NET SDK 9+ automatically detects the OIDC token from the GitHub Actions environment when no `--api-key` is provided. If you're on an older SDK, you may need `--api-key az` as a placeholder — but upgrading to SDK 9+ is recommended.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"02c68890-9566-4c2e-8b4d-7ab82478bf71","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. I don't have a workflow file to look at, so I'll provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":543},"id":"00fa242b-7664-4766-9b78-74c03850c0f0","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:36.950Z","parentId":"fd299bbc-12cd-48a9-85d5-7d9650f00be6"}
